---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Prose from "../components/Prose.astro";
import { site, absoluteUrl } from "../site.config";

const title = "Terms & Conditions";
const description = `${site.name} terms and conditions — the simple terms for using a free, browser-based photo eraser. Acceptable use, disclaimers, and your responsibilities.`;

const termsSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "@id": absoluteUrl("/terms"),
  name: `${site.name} Terms & Conditions`,
  url: absoluteUrl("/terms"),
  description,
  isPartOf: { "@id": `${site.url}/#website` },
};

const breadcrumbSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  itemListElement: [
    { "@type": "ListItem", position: 1, name: "Home", item: absoluteUrl("/") },
    { "@type": "ListItem", position: 2, name: "Terms & Conditions", item: absoluteUrl("/terms") },
  ],
};

const lastUpdated = new Date().toLocaleDateString("en-US", {
  year: "numeric",
  month: "long",
  day: "numeric",
});
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} jsonLd={[termsSchema, breadcrumbSchema]}>
  <Header />

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 sm:py-16">
    <nav class="text-sm text-[var(--color-fg-subtle)]" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-[var(--color-fg)]">Home</a>
      <span class="px-1.5">/</span>
      <span class="text-[var(--color-fg-muted)]">Terms &amp; Conditions</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="mt-6">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
        Terms &amp; Conditions
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-[var(--color-fg-subtle)]">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="mt-10">
      <Prose>
        <h2>1. Acceptance of terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing or using {site.name} (the "Service") at
          <code>{site.domain}</code>, you agree to these Terms &amp; Conditions.
          If you don't agree, please don't use the Service. Because the Service is
          free and requires no account, your use of it constitutes acceptance.
        </p>

        <h2>2. What the Service is</h2>
        <p>
          {site.name} is a free, browser-based tool that lets you remove objects
          from your own photos using AI that runs entirely on your device. Your
          images are processed locally and are never uploaded to us. There is no
          account, no subscription, and no charge.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Your responsibilities</h2>
        <p>You agree that you will:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Only edit photos you own or have the right to edit;</li>
          <li>Not use the Service to create or distribute content that is unlawful, infringing, defamatory, or that violates the privacy or rights of others;</li>
          <li>Not use the Service to produce misleading or deceptive imagery intended to harm, defraud, or impersonate;</li>
          <li>Comply with all applicable laws in your use of the Service and any images you create with it.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You are solely responsible for the photos you edit and how you use the
          results. Since everything happens on your device, what you do with the
          tool is entirely within your control — and your responsibility.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Your photos remain yours.</strong> We claim no ownership of, and
          acquire no rights to, any image you open or create with the Service —
          we never even receive them. The {site.name} name, website, design, and
          underlying code are owned by us or our licensors; the project's source
          code is made available under the license stated in its
          <a href={site.githubRepo} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">public repository</a>.
          Third-party AI models used by the Service are subject to their own
          respective licenses.
        </p>

        <h2>5. No warranty</h2>
        <p>
          The Service is provided <strong>"as is" and "as available," without
          warranties of any kind</strong>, express or implied, including but not
          limited to merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and
          non-infringement. AI-based object removal is inherently imperfect:
          results vary by image, and the tool may produce artifacts or
          unsatisfactory output. We do not warrant that the Service will be
          uninterrupted, error-free, or that results will meet your expectations.
          Performance depends on your device and browser.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, {site.name} and its operator
          shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special,
          consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of data, profits, or
          goodwill, arising out of or related to your use of (or inability to use)
          the Service — even if advised of the possibility of such damages.
          Because the Service is provided free of charge, our total aggregate
          liability for any claim relating to the Service shall not exceed
          <strong>USD $0</strong>.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Third-party links and advertising</h2>
        <p>
          The site may contain links to third-party websites and may display
          advertising on informational pages to keep the Service free. We are not
          responsible for the content, policies, or practices of any third-party
          sites or advertisers.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Changes to the Service and these terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may modify, suspend, or discontinue any part of the Service at any
          time without notice. We may also update these Terms from time to time;
          the "last updated" date above reflects the latest version. Continued
          use after changes constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Governing law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of {site.jurisdiction}, without
          regard to its conflict-of-laws principles. Any disputes shall be subject
          to the courts of competent jurisdiction in {site.jurisdiction}.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these Terms? Email
          <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`}>{site.contactEmail}</a>. See also
          our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>
      </Prose>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
